items.title: Starbucks’ CEO is ditching a merit system and giving all salaried staff a flat 2% pay raise instead

items.title: Beyond snubbing Tinder, Bumble, and casual flings, more than half of Gen Z is spending $0 monthly on dating, BofA finds
items.description: Gen Z’s economic anxiety—as well as disinterest in casual dating—has led many young people to spend little to nothing on dates.
